<p><span style=" font-family: Sylfaen;"><span style=" font-size: medium;">1) Buy one or two books that are similar to the type of material you want to be able to speed read. These will be your books for practice reading.</span></span><span style=" font-size: medium;"></span></p>
<p><span style=" font-family: Sylfaen;"><span style=" font-size: medium;">2) Commit for at least 3 weeks to practice either speed or comprehension exercises (as outlined in Practice Reading) for fifteen minutes a day on your practice books.</span></span><span style=" font-size: medium;"></span></p>
<p><span style=" font-family: Sylfaen;"><span style=" font-size: medium;">3) Also commit to using your finger as a pointer for the next two weeks on all written material on paper.</span></span><span style=" font-size: medium;"></span></p>
<p><span style=" font-family: Sylfaen;"><span style=" font-size: medium;">4) Practice active reading with at least one of your textbooks once a week.</span></span><span style=" font-size: medium;"></span></p>
